---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Members"
permalink: /members/
---

<article class="members-hub">
  <a class="back" href="/">← Reading journey</a>

  <h1>Members</h1>

  <p class="lede">
    Resources for current R/W Book Club members.
  </p>

  <h2>Current members</h2>
  <ul class="member-list">
    {% for m in currentMembers %}
      <li>
        <a href="/members/{{ m.slug }}/">{{ m.name }}</a>
        {% if m.pickedCount %}<span class="pick-count">{{ m.pickedCount }} pick{% if m.pickedCount != 1 %}s{% endif %}</span>{% endif %}
      </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>

  <h2>AI / LLM context</h2>
  <p>
    Want to ask an AI chatbot for a book recommendation based on our reading
    history? Paste one of these links into any conversation to give the model
    full context about what we've read.
  </p>
  <ul class="resource-list">
    <li>
      <a href="/llms.txt">llms.txt</a>
      <span class="resource-desc">Compact index of every book, with a URL to a detailed text file for each one. Start here.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/books.json">books.json</a>
      <span class="resource-desc">Structured JSON, one row per book, for analytical or cross-book queries.</span>
    </li>
  </ul>
</article>
